### [1 John Chapter 1](../../../bib/kjv/jo1001.htm#001.md)

[1 John 1:7](../../../bib/kjv/jo1001.htm#007.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_007">jo1 1:7</span></span>

light

What it is to "walk in the light" is explained by ([Jo1
1:8-10](../../../bib/kjv/jo1001.htm#008).md). "All things. . .are made
manifest by the light". ([Eph 5:13](../../../bib/kjv/eph005.htm#013).md).
The presence of God brings the consciousness of sin in the nature ([Jo1
1:8](../../../bib/kjv/jo1001.htm#008).md) and sins in the life. ([Jo1
1:9](../../../bib/kjv/jo1001.htm#009).md); ([Jo1
1:10](../../../bib/kjv/jo1001.htm#010).md). The blood of Christ is the
divine provision for both. To walk in the light is to live in fellowship
with the Father and the Son. Sin interrupts, but confession restores
that fellowship. Immediate confession keeps the fellowship unbroken.

light

